Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
getValidPowerSwitchLocation(25.10)          getValidPowerSwitchLocation(25.10)

Name
       getValidPowerSwitchLocation  -  Returns  a  valid location of the power
       switch cells according to the specified placement grid, cell name,  and
       nearest location

Syntax
       getValidPowerSwitchLocation

       -help

       -cell <cell_name>-loc <location>[-orient <string>]

       [-searchArea <string>]

       Returns  a  valid  location  of the power switch cells according to the
       specified placement grid, cell name, and nearest location.  This  valid
       location of the power switch cells can be used to specify offsets while
       using the addPowerSwitch command.

Parameters
       -help  Prints  a  brief  description that includes the type and default
              information for each getValidPowerSwitchLocation parameter.  For
              a  detailed  description  of the command and all its parameters,
              use the man command:

              man getValidPowerSwitchLocation

       -cell <cell_name>
              Specifies the name of the power switch cell whose valid location
              needs to be identified.

       -loc <location>
              Specifies the nearest location from  where  the  valid  location
              needs to be identified.

       -orient <string>
              Specifies  the  orientation.  The  orientation can be one of the
              following: r0,  r90,  r180,  r270,  mx,  mx90,  my, and  my90.

       -searchArea <string>
              Specifies the area within which the valid location needs  to  be
              identified.

Example
       The  following  command identifies a valid location for the HSWX1 power
       switch cell:

       getValidPowerSwitchLocation -cell HSWX1 -orient MX -loc {382 970}

       Following is the output of the above command:

       382.0350 970.0750 MX

Related Information
